  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#4A2A12">I think verant is taking this a bit too far now.  If you are included in a raid that gets a drop then you should be able to wear it if you are the correct class / size (notice size and not race) If you think of real world situations a warrior would not wear a robe (and thus class based equipment) and an ogre couldnt wear a breastplate that was formerly a gnomes (thus size based) but to get into needing a certain amount of skill or a certain lvl to wear an item is just stupid. i hope verant realizes that by making items no drop they reduce twinking and in most cases anihilate it.  They shouldrealize this and remove these extra requirements that just confuse and anger us.  There is no need<br><br></td></tr>
